commitResults.messageTitle: Add JavaFX functionality.
commitResults.messageBody:
Edit build.gradle to add JavaFX functionality.

Duke's constructor had to be changed to take in no arguments. Previously, a String representing the saveFilePath was passed into the constructor, but this had to be changed to accommodate the JavaFX launch code. Now, the saveFilePath can still be edited, but any change has to be made directly to the static variable, instead of being passed to the Duke constructor directly. An example is given in the main() method of Duke.

commitResults.messageBody: Original Command#execute would save the TaskList object. Refactored to remove this functionality as not all subclasses require this behaviour. Makes more sense to explicitly move the saving functionality to the subclasses instead.

commitResults.messageTitle: Updated Parser. Replace ByeCommand with SaveCommand as "bye" no longer closes the window. Instead, typing "save" will not explicitly save the data.
commitResults.messageBody: Note that this is not technically a refactoring as external behaviour is changed.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update tests to reflect change from ByeCommand to SaveCommand.
Refactor Command class to get rid of dead code.
commitResults.messageBody: More specifically, the isExit boolean is no longer necessary. It was initially meant as a flag to indicate whether the CLI Duke ought to exit from the while loop, but in the GUI Duke, this functionality is no longer supported.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor Dialogbox.
commitResults.messageBody: Original Dialogbox had a boolean to determine whether to flip the dialogbox (user vs duke) and which fxml file to load. Refactoring Dialogbox into 2 different classes - UserDialogBox and DukeDialogBox - is cleaner, since there already exist 2 different fxml files detailing their layouts and their respectively css style classes. This is in line with the 'Remove Flag Argument' refactoring principle stated on refactoring.com/catalog/
